data.title: Good service
data.text: Smiling faces. Lamb is the best and the mojito. Is really good to share with friends. Paella is not reccommendedgiir special  occassion .Be sure that you have a designated driver should you decide to stay for happy hour and beyonf😏

data.title: Good Cuban Food
data.text: If you're looking for a new latin flavor, try this! We've been here several times and have had good food and service. Look forward to going back.

data.title: Standard Americanized Cuban
data.text: I have eaten lunch here several times, and have sampled all their sandwiches and a few entrees.  The more typical Cuban food is competently prepared, but somewhat americanized.  Still reasonably priced lunch spot with a decent atmosphere.

data.title: Outstanding Cuban Food
data.text: Havana was a perfect place for an informal after-work dinner with colleagues. Although the decor is simple and colorful, the food is complex and well-prepared. I stuck to small plates, including the best Cuban sandwich I've ever come across. Others were equally impressed with the quality of their dishes. If I get back to Walnut Creek, Havana will be at the top of my dining list.

data.title: Amazing Cuban food!  Awesome mojitos!
data.text: Had lunch w/hubby during Walnut Creek restaurant week.  Restaurant was slammed with fans getting in on the $10 lunch specials!  We had the ropa vieja and the cod - both were outstanding!  the flan was great!  chocolate dessert was a little heavy but also delicious.  pineapple blood orange mojito was fantastic!

data.title: Walnut Creek is HAPPENING
data.text: Great atmosphere. The mojitos are amazing. The food was really good and complemented the drinks perfectly. Would for sure go again.

data.title: Monday Half off Mojito!
data.text: Nice place to hang out but tends to get busy. It used to be better quality food but still not too bad.

data.title: Mojito Mondays
data.text:
If you like spicy Cuban food this it the place to eat in Walnut Creek.  Nice atmosphere and plenty of seeting. Mojito Mondays are awesome and sometimes crowded.  They often have a sponsor such as Captain Morgan or Cruzan on Mondays.  The representatives of the sponsors provide samples of their various beverages.  
Be sure to try the items on the appetizer menu.  I often just eat the apps and have a Mojito or two.

data.title: Nice dinner date with hubby
data.text:
Very impressed!  Anniversary dinner here was a treat.  Quality ingredients cooked nicely. The scallops app is a star plate!  Calamari, fresh, flavorful and cooked nicely with a spicy guacamole sauce.  My banana leaf wrapped sea bass was a tad over, but not horrible.  Paella, again, fresh ingredients, delicate flavor, I would say needed a tad of salt to bring it to its height.  

Happened to be mojito Monday, $4 mojitos which were well made with a kick!

Solid service as well

All around solid 4 stars!  Impressed from a Philly Foodie

data.title: Crabcake, Empanada
data.text: The crabcake was really great, and so was the little empanadas, bbqued shrimps were tasty, then we had the fried plantain. This was just a snack, in the niddle of the afternoon. Dinner must also be great here.

data.title: Excellent Mojitos and tasty food
data.text: Mondays are 1/2 priced Mojitos including pitchers so it's a great place to go for 2 or more.  Food is terrific (love the Ahi).  The only downside for me is that the main space is very loud ... which can be a good thing.  We have taken over the entire place for a holiday office party and everyone had a ball

data.title: Hanging with the Guys
data.text: The food, drinks, service and ambiance was exceptional.   It is great for families. .they played great music in the background,  however it wasn't so loud as to impact an intimate conversation.   Can't wait to go again.
